            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science is a vital economic driver in NC-11, with $1,004,139 in obligations (FY23-25) supporting institutions like Southwestern Community College and Western Carolina University.\n* This $9 billion request ensures the U.S. maintains its strategic lead over China's rapidly expanding space program, securing our role in setting 21st-century exploration norms.\n* Every dollar invested in NASA Science returns $3 to the American economy, fostering a high-tech workforce and a STEM pipeline that powers local innovation.\n* Funding restores stability to the aerospace workforce following the disruptions of FY2026, protecting decades of bipartisan investment in national prestige and scientific discovery.",
